<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Single specimen, with white axis and polyps; polyps standing perpendicular to the axis when alive (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Mopseidae sp. CCZ _ 088 A in situ image B whole colony attached to a nodule C detail of polyps before preservation. Scale bars: 5 cm (A); 2 cm (B); 5 mm (C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17A</figureCitation>
). Colony is long, ~ 45 cm tall, and unbranched (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Mopseidae sp. CCZ _ 088 A in situ image B whole colony attached to a nodule C detail of polyps before preservation. Scale bars: 5 cm (A); 2 cm (B); 5 mm (C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17A, B</figureCitation>
). Polyps are tall, ~ 2 mm, clavate, and standing parallel to the branch (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Mopseidae sp. CCZ _ 088 A in situ image B whole colony attached to a nodule C detail of polyps before preservation. Scale bars: 5 cm (A); 2 cm (B); 5 mm (C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
